{"comments":"UTC Timestamp — Milliseconds since Unix epoch (1970-01-01T00:00:00Z).\n\nThis is the canonical timestamp type for attestations. It provides:\n- Unambiguous point-in-time representation\n- No timezone complexity\n- Direct serialization to/from Number\n- Deterministic ordering\n\n## Why Milliseconds?\n\n- Sufficient precision for scheduling (sub-second events)\n- Matches JavaScript Date.now() semantics\n- Fits in Number without precision loss until year 275760\n- Standard for JSON/API timestamps\n\n## Representation\n\nWe use Number (IEEE 754 double) rather than Int because:\n- Int is 32-bit, overflows in 2038\n- Number safely represents integers up to 2^53\n- Milliseconds since epoch easily exceeds 32-bit range\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Timestamp"],"Timestamp"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Timestamp.purs","start":[82,1]},"title":"eqTimestamp"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Timestamp"],"Timestamp"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Timestamp.purs","start":[83,1]},"title":"ordTimestamp"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Timestamp"],"Timestamp"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,2